      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUMBLE STRIP NZ (6) is in fine form having overcome tougher barriers to win his last two outings at this circuit and distance, racing parked from the back row before getting home by 3.6m last week. Should be at his peak and looks well placed to land the hat trick. Former Kiwi DOUBLE PARKED NZ (8) drew on the back row and finished midfield when making his WA debut at Group Three level two weeks ago. Draws deep but goes very well second-up with two wins and a placing from three attempts so should be improved. BETTOR ARCADE (12) is looming as a threat after three straight placings at this circuit and distance, working from a wider barrier when beaten only 2m last week. The ace draw can see LILLIE QUEEN (1) continue her consistent form.",
